title: Two seriously injured in head-on crash near TN high school
text:
Two seriously injured in head-on crash near TN high school
The crash has closed the Highway 76 in that area as emergency crews work.
Published: Jul. 2, 2025 at 8:49 PM CDT|Updated: 3 hours ago
WHITE HOUSE, Tenn. (WSMV) - Two people were seriously injured in a head-on crash in Robertson County, according to Smokey Barn News.
SBN reports the head-on collision occurred on Highway 76 near White House Heritage High School on Wednesday night.
Here are instructions on how to watch WSMV4 live on various platforms.
Two people were taken to hospitals with serious injuries, while one other person involved in the crash refused medical care.
The crash has closed the Highway 76 in that area as emergency crews work, SBN said.
Drivers are being asked to avoid the area and watch for emergency vehicles.
This is a developing story.
